snippet.title: MEGHAN MARKLE Suffers Miscarriage || MARADONA Dies At 60 || Johnny Depp Axed From Fantastic Beasts
snippet.description:
#maradona #johnnydepp #amberheard

Nigeria entered recession for the second time in four years, ASUU has called off its eight-month-long strike, Meghan Markle revealed she suffered a miscarriage, Grammyannounced 2021 nominations list with Burna Boy getting a consecutive second nod. Meanwhile, Mads Mikkelsen has been confirmed as Johnny Depp’s replacement for the next Fantastic Beasts movie and Argentine football legend Diego Maradona died of cardiac arrest at 60. These and more are part of our stories for you this week. Buckle up?

01:38 - ASUU calls off 8-month long strike
02:22 - Yakubu Gowon refutes allegations from UK Parliament
03:00 - Meghan Markle suffered a miscarriage in July 2020
03:55 - Moe and Eromz share photos from dinner date
04:23 - 9ice apologizes over viral video
05:14 - Burna receives Grammy nomination again
06:33 - Davido's A BETTER TIME debuts on billboard 200 chart
06:58 - Wizkid's JORO surpasses 72 million streams on YouTube
07:12 - Mads Mikkelsen replaces Johnny Depp as Grindelwald in FANTASTIC BEASTS over Amber Heard 'wife beater' case
08:02 - Ready Player Two set to drop
08:18 - Undertaker officially announces retirement from wrestling
08:47 - Sports Update 
14:58 - Coronavirus update in numbers
